    <section id="about">
    <h3> About 4 Ocean </h3></div>
        <p>Our ultimate goal is to remove as much plastic out of the ocean as possible<br>
         in order to save the marine life that has been around for decades. 4Ocean believes<br>
        that for our world to be a better place, our ocean's need to be taken care off. Over the<br>
        years we have been trying to help clean but make people aaware of the problem we face<br>
        which is Climate change. Climate change has caused chaotic events which are ireversible,<br>
        such as the glaciers melting due to extreme heat, which not only causes the ocean's to <br>
        rise but has also increased the water tempretures. Due to the water tempretures increasing,<br>
        sea turtle repoduction has changed as they rely on the tempretures to determine the sex. <br>
        Due to warmer tempretures turtles have been producing majority female hatchlings, which is <br>
        ideal as the male turtles are becoming less as they need cooler tempretures to hatch. Therefore<br>
        if we do not take a stance to fight climate change we could loose sea turtles to extinction.</p>
                </div>x
    </section>


    <section id="explore">
<div class="container">
    <span class="text first-text"> Why are Turtles so</span>
    <span class="text sec-text">Important?</span>
</div>

<div class="paragraph1">
    <p> Turtles are known to be one of the oldest creatures to live on Earth, they have played vital roles <br>
        in maintaining the health of the world's oceans for more than 100 million years. Their roles range <br>
        from maintaining the coral reef production and their ecosystems, to being the ideal transportation for<br>
         essential nutrients to be collected from oceans to beaches and coastal dunes. Without the turtles many <br>
         of the species of coral reefs and ecosystems would not be able to survive, turtles have thus played a <br>
          huge helping hand it keeping the oceanâ€™s in order.
        <br>
    <br> </p>
</div>
</section>


